│ │  X/Y-axis accelerometer: MEMS, ±16g, 16-bit ADC                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  IMU package: STMicro LSM6DSO32                                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  Tech spec explicitly states: "Z-axis positional accuracy is lower than X/Y  │
│ due to   │                                                                     │
│ │  the 14-bit ADC on the Z-axis accelerometer (vs. 16-bit on X/Y). This is a   │
│ KNOWN    │                                                                     │
│ │  LIMITATION of the current IMU package... partially compensated by optical   │
│ sensor     │                                                                   │
│ │  fusion. Accuracy degrades further in volumes exceeding 10m on the Z-axis."  │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │ RECOMMENDED ENGINEERING CHANGES:                                             │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  (a) Replace STMicro LSM6DSO32 with an IMU offering uniform 16-bit ADC       │
│ across all   │                                                                 │
│ │      axes (e.g., Bosch BMI323 or TDK InvenSense ICM-42688-P).                │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  (b) Interim firmware mitigation: increase optical sensor fusion weight on   │
│ Z-axis    │                                                                    │
│ │      to compensate for IMU drift; add real-time Z-drift detection and auto-  │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │      recalibration trigger.                                                  │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  (c) Update marketing/spec sheet to clearly communicate Z-axis limitation    │
│ until      │                                                                   │
│ │      hardware fix ships (prevents repeat-complaint pattern seen with         │
│ Customer 51).   │                                                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │ COST IMPACT:                                                                 │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  • IMU swap: +$3–6/unit (comparable package footprint, minimal PCB rework).  │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  • Firmware interim fix: $0 BOM.                                             │
│ │                                                                              │
│ │  • At $749.99 MSRP, the +$3–6 increase is <1% of unit cost — easily          │
│ absorbed.       │                                                              │
│ │  • Risk: SenseField 360 is the highest-margin product line. Z-axis issues    │
│ threaten   │                                                                   │
│ │    clinical/research credibility (medical rehab, surgical rehearsal          │
│ customers).       │                                                            │
│ │    Customer 51 had 2 units fail — potential for escalation to clinical       │
│ advisory.     │                                                                │
